After solving the equity, the value of debt is solved below: 

&nbsp;

$$\begin{aligned}
\textbf{Debt}&=\text{Asset's Value}-\text{Equity}\\[15pt]
&=\$18,100-\$5,324\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\$12,776}
\end{aligned}$$

The computed value of equity is deducted from the asset's value to determine the value of debt. 

Thus, the value of the debt is $12,776.

After solving the equity, the value of debt is solved below: 

&nbsp;

$$\begin{aligned}
\textbf{Debt}&=\text{Asset's Value}-\text{Equity}\\[15pt]
&=\$19,000-\$5,250\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\$13,750}
\end{aligned}$$

The computed value of equity is deducted from the asset's value to determine the value of debt. 

Thus, the value of the debt is $13,750.
